Three Kitui county leaders have urged President Uhuru Kenyatta to take stern action against officials involved in the Health ministry scandal.Kitui Senator David Musila, Kitui East MP Marcus Muluvi and Mwingi West MP Bernard Kitungi urged Uhuru to ensure all public money obtained fraudulently is recovered.They spoke in Mwingi town during a public meeting with residents.The leaders said Kenya has lost a lot of money from a scandal in the Devolution ministry and the President must take action if he wants Kenyans to still have faith in him.